Agent Brief — “Scrubby Public Pricing Section (Website) — Direct Charges”

Role: You are the Public Pricing Section Agent for Scrubby. Deliver a clean, conversion-focused pricing block for our website that matches Launch v1.2 and Stripe Connect: Direct charges economics.

Context (must adhere):

Plans at launch (public):

Free (default): 10% per booking on marketplace and BYO. No monthly fee.

Pro (Founding Beta): $0 for 90 days → $39/mo. 0% on BYO bookings. Marketplace remains 10%.

Stripe billing model: Direct charges (customer is charged on the provider’s connected account).

The provider pays Stripe processing & dispute fees; Scrubby’s application fee (our commission) is taken separately on the same transaction.

Stripe fees appear in the provider payout breakdown (not on the customer receipt).

Payouts: Weekly by default; instant payouts optional (provider-paid Stripe fee).

Taxes: NY grooming defaults to taxable; provider is merchant of record for tax remittance.

Not at launch: No consumer booking fee. Do not mention the hidden “Hybrid” plan anywhere.

Deliverables

Public pricing section (choose one):

Option A (preferred): React component (default export), semantic HTML + Tailwind classes.

Option B: Single self-contained HTML/CSS file (semantic HTML; embedded CSS acceptable).

Exact copy below (you may adjust punctuation/line breaks only).

FAQ accordion (5–6 Qs) using the entries below.

Footnotes/disclaimers area (must reflect Direct charges details).

CTA row with two actions: “Book a 10-minute demo” and “Get started free”.

Exact copy (use verbatim; minor line-break edits OK)

Headline:
Simple, transparent pricing for indie groomers.

Subhead:
Start free—pay only on bookings. Upgrade when you want 0% fees on your own clients.

Free

$0 per month

10% per booking on marketplace and BYO

Client profiles & notes, calendar & availability, deposits, cancellation/no-show rules

Basic reminders, 150 SMS/mo included (then $0.02/SMS)

Weekly payouts; standard chat/email support

Pro — Founding Beta

$0 for 90 days, then $39/month

0% on BYO bookings (marketplace remains 10%)

Two-way SMS & automations, recurring appointments

Invoices/partial prepay, revenue snapshot

QuickBooks CSV export, 2 staff seats & roles

500 SMS/mo included (then $0.02/SMS), priority chat (US hours)

Definitions (inline microcopy under cards):

Marketplace booking: a new customer finds you via Scrubby search/ads/referrals.

BYO booking: your own client uses your unique link/QR or comes from your imported list.

Footnotes (render at bottom):

Stripe Connect (Direct charges): the customer is charged on your connected account. You pay Stripe processing & dispute fees; Scrubby’s application fee (our commission) is taken separately on the same transaction.

Stripe fees appear in your provider payout breakdown; customers do not see Stripe fees on their receipt.

Weekly payouts by default (Mon 12:00am ET cutoff; payouts start Wed). Instant payouts optional (Stripe fee applies).

New York grooming services are taxable by default. You are the merchant of record for tax remittance.

FAQ (accordion)

What’s the difference between marketplace and BYO bookings?
Marketplace = new customers who find you via Scrubby search/ads/referrals. BYO = your own clients via your unique link/QR or from your imported list.

Does Pro remove all fees?
Pro removes fees on BYO bookings only. Marketplace bookings remain 10%.

Who pays Stripe processing fees?
With Direct charges, you (the provider) pay Stripe processing & dispute fees. They show up in your payout breakdown, not on the customer receipt.

When do I get paid?
Weekly by default (Mon 12:00am ET cutoff; payouts start Wed). Instant payouts are optional via Stripe (additional Stripe fee applies).

Is New York sales tax handled?
Yes. NY grooming defaults to taxable. Tax appears on the customer’s receipt. You remain the merchant of record for tax remittance.

Can I switch plans later?
Yes—start on Free and upgrade to Pro anytime.

Design/spec requirements

Two pricing cards (Free, Pro). Pro should have a subtle “Most Popular” badge.

Clear price typography; concise feature lists; short “What’s included” checklist.

Place the definitions line (Marketplace vs BYO) right under the cards.

FAQ accordion under the pricing cards; Footnotes beneath the FAQ.

CTA row pinned at the end: “Book a 10-minute demo” and “Get started free.”

Include “Questions?” with support@scrubby.app
 and {Calendly URL} near the CTAs.

Accessibility: semantic headings, keyboard-navigable accordion/buttons, visible focus states, sufficient color contrast.

Responsiveness: mobile-first; cards stack on small screens; readable footnotes.

Success criteria

Content exactly matches this brief (no extra plans or consumer fees).

Direct charges language is present and accurate.

Renders cleanly on mobile and desktop; basic accessibility checks pass.

Easy to drop into a Next.js page or a static site.

Placeholders to fill: {Calendly URL}, {support@scrubby.app}, {start_now_url}.

Output: Provide the full React component (Option A) or a single HTML file (Option B). Include a one-paragraph note on how to embed it into a Next.js or plain HTML page.